last_episode_to_air.name: Au Revoir
last_episode_to_air.overview: In order to help Neal carry out a risky heist, Peter must involve himself in a dangerous con.

name: White Collar
overview: Neal Caffrey, a con man, forger and thief, is captured after a three-year game of cat and mouse with the FBI. With only months left serving a four-year sentence, he escapes to look for Kate, his girlfriend. Peter Burke, the FBI agent who initially captured Caffrey, finds and returns him to prison. This time, Caffrey proposes a deal with the FBI, as part of a work-release program. After some hesitation, Burke agrees, and thus begins this unconventional arrangement where Caffrey helps Burke apprehend white collar criminals.

seasons.name: Season 1
seasons.overview: Charming con man Neal Caffey escapes from a maximum-security prison, only to be recaptured by his nemesis, FBI Agent Peter Burke. With few options, Caffey agrees to help the bureau bring down other elusive criminals in exchange for his eventual freedom. But before long, Caffey finds himself playing a game of cat and mouse with those who want him back in prison or dead.

seasons.name: Season 2
seasons.overview: Reeling from the death of his girlfriend, Neal struggles to unlock the secret behind a mysterious music box and find Kate’s killer, even as his partnership with Peter begins to crumble.

seasons.name: Season 3
seasons.overview: Suave con man turned FBI consultant Neal Caffrey is racing to stay one step ahead of the feds even as he helps his partner, Agent Peter Burke, bring down some of the world's most clever criminals. The stakes are at an all-time high as Neal struggles to come to terms with his own checkered past, but will his greatest con cost him everything?

seasons.name: Season 4
seasons.overview: Facing the uncertain future of his partnership with FBI Agent Peter Burke, Neal sheds his tracking anklet and disappears into thin air. But the Feds aren't done with him and Neal is hardly ready for retirement. Back in action, Neal ponders the future as Season Four delves deeper into the stunning secrets of his mysterious past.

seasons.name: Season 5
seasons.overview: $1.8 million in gold coins is missing, an elusive precious diamond is about to be found, and Neal Caffrey has a new handler – and a new love interest. But all is fair in love and crime, and the closer Neal gets to the mysterious Rebecca Lowe, the greater the danger for everyone in his life.

seasons.name: Season 6
seasons.overview: The tension has never been greater as Neal Caffrey re-teams with FBI agent Peter Burke in their most ambitious sting operation yet — infiltrating a sophisticated gang of deadly thieves. With Elizabeth Burke pregnant, Neal desperate for his freedom, and amidst pressure from Mozzie for Neal to cut ties with the FBI, the scheme unfolds, culminating in the series’ most shocking plot twist of all.

tagline: To solve the toughest crimes, hire the smartest criminal.

episodes.name: Pilot
episodes.overview: When the trail of elusive criminal "The Dutchman" dead ends, FBI Agent Peter Burke teams up with a most unlikely partner to catch him - the imprisoned Neal Caffrey.

episodes.name: Threads
episodes.overview: Neal and Peter infiltrate New York's Fashion Week to stop a security data which is woven in the fabric of a model's dress, from being sold by a criminal.

episodes.name: Book of Hours
episodes.overview: The disappearance of a precious bible creates an interesting union when a New York Mafia kingpin enlists the help of Peter and the FBI in tracking down his beloved artifact. But while rooting out the thief, Neal finds himself in a tango with a sexy female villain and must decide where his loyalty truly lies.

episodes.name: Flip of the Coin
episodes.overview: Peter thinks he’s in for it when Elizabeth shows up at the office with her friend Dana in tow. But Peter isn’t the one in trouble this time; it’s Dana’s husband, Captain John Mitchell, who is in the hot seat.

episodes.name: The Portrait
episodes.overview: When an expensive portrait is stolen from a young woman, Peter and Neal set a sting for the cunning and deadly culprit. Neal must uncover the secret truth of the portrait's origin even as the net tightens around the villain ... and around Neal himself!

episodes.name: All In
episodes.overview: Thrust into the seedy underbelly of New York's Chinatown, Peter and Neal must navigate vicious Triads, mysterious Interpol agents, and a game of Pai Gow in order to capture their target.

episodes.name: Free Fall
episodes.overview: The FBI investigates a spectacular jewelry heist and all the clues point to Neal. Now Peter must figure out if his "partner" is telling the truth or if Neal is pulling a con of his own.

episodes.name: Hard Sell
episodes.overview: Neal must infiltrate a company of corrupt Wall Street brokers to preserve his deal with the FBI. When Peter is forced to go undercover alongside him, a discovery is made that could change their partnership forever.

episodes.name: Bad Judgment
episodes.overview: When Peter and Neal discover that an estate judge committing mortgage fraud is also connected to Fowler, they devise a plan to bring them both down.

episodes.name: Vital Signs
episodes.overview: When June's niece suffers renal trauma, Neal stumbles upon a cruel scheme to harvest human organs and brings the case to Peter.

episodes.name: Home Invasion
episodes.overview: To avoid an international conflict, Peter and Neal have to find a thief who is stealing pieces to a valuable collection.

episodes.name: Bottlenecked
episodes.overview: An old rival of Neal's lays down a challenge: to see if either of them can create an impossible forgery. But as the rival uses brutal and deadly tactics to achieve his ends, Neal quickly realizes that much more is at stake than bragging rights!

episodes.name: Front Man
episodes.overview: Neal helps an old friend whose daughter has been kidnapped, without realizing that it's all a trap from an old enemy.

episodes.name: Out of the Box
episodes.overview: Neal and Alex attempt to recover a music box from the Italian Consulate. Peter and Diana try to take down Fowler

1.name: Season 1
1.overview: Charming con man Neal Caffey escapes from a maximum-security prison, only to be recaptured by his nemesis, FBI Agent Peter Burke. With few options, Caffey agrees to help the bureau bring down other elusive criminals in exchange for his eventual freedom. But before long, Caffey finds himself playing a game of cat and mouse with those who want him back in prison or dead.

episodes.name: Withdrawal
episodes.overview: Peter and Neal try to stay a step ahead of a sophisticated bank robber. But once alarms are set off throughout the city, the guys realize they're dealing with a true professional.

episodes.name: Need to Know
episodes.overview: Neal goes undercover as a political "fixer" in order to bring down a corrupt politician. Diana and Peter's lead brings them to an unidentified man who escapes their pursuit. It is also revealed that Peter had Diana keep the music box's location hidden even from Peter himself. Neal begins to suspect that Peter is investigating the plane explosion behind his back.

episodes.name: Copycat Caffrey
episodes.overview: Peter sends Neal back to school after someone copycats one of his old schemes. Alex returns with some bad news. Diana discovers the music box is hiding something. Peter and Diana set out to find the missing key, which is the last piece of the music box that Alex gives Neal before leaving for Italy. Aidan Quinn guest stars as a criminology professor.

episodes.name: By the Book
episodes.overview: When Mozzie believes someone he cares about has been kidnapped, he turns to Peter and Neal for help.

episodes.name: Unfinished Business
episodes.overview: In order to save the life of an insurance investigator named Sara Ellis, Neal and Peter have to find out why a real-estate mogul put a price on her head.

episodes.name: In the Red
episodes.overview: The arrest of a jewel thief leads Peter and Neal toward a much more heinous extortion case against adoptive parents.

episodes.name: Prisoner's Dilemma
episodes.overview: Joe Morton! An FBI Agent is accused of selling witness locations during criminal trials, and the U.S. Marshals ask Peter and Neal for help tracking down the suspect

episodes.name: Company Man
episodes.overview: Neal and Peter must go undercover into the world of corporate espionage after a tech company's head researcher is murdered.

episodes.name: Point Blank
episodes.overview: Neal orchestrates an elaborate con to bring himself face to face with Kate's murderer.

episodes.name: Burke's Seven
episodes.overview: Mozzie narrowly escapes death and Neal uses his contacts to help Peter find Mozzie's shooter Julian Larssen. However, Larssen manages to blame Peter instead and is released. Suspended from the FBI, Peter enlists the help of Neal, Jones, Diana, Sara, Mozzie and even Elizabeth to run a sting to finally catch Larssen and to clear his name.

episodes.name: Forging Bonds
episodes.overview: Peter goes back to the time he arrested Neal for the first time. In the meantime, Neal remembers meeting Kate and Mozzie.

episodes.name: What Happens in Burma
episodes.overview: Peter and Neal work to free a diplomat's son, who has been taken into custody in Burma for a crime he didn't commit. The case requires the duo to use diplomatic laws to their advantage in order to overcome the obstacles facing them.

episodes.name: Countermeasures
episodes.overview: Neal is suspicious when an old friend of June's husband is released from jail and shows up for a visit.

episodes.name: Payback
episodes.overview: Matthew Keller, Neal's imprisoned rival, contacts Neal and Peter to make a deal. However, the two have to realize Keller set them up to kidnap Peter and to force Neal to bargain with Jason Lang, Keller's former partner turned adversary.

episodes.name: Power Play
episodes.overview: Peter and Neal assume each other's identities to uncover a collusion scheme.

episodes.name: Under the Radar
episodes.overview: Neal gets closer to finding out the truth about Kate's death.

2.name: Season 2
2.overview: Reeling from the death of his girlfriend, Neal struggles to unlock the secret behind a mysterious music box and find Kate’s killer, even as his partnership with Peter begins to crumble.

episodes.name: On Guard
episodes.overview: Despite their newly-arisen trust issues, Neal and Peter have to work together to catch a thief who took his stash out of the Federal Reserve.

episodes.name: Where There's a Will
episodes.overview: Peter and Neal find a treasure map on a forged will, and soon enter a race to locate the treasure and save the daughter of the beneficiary.

episodes.name: Deadline
episodes.overview: Diana goes undercover to protect a magazine journalist; Peter and Neal investigate a pharmaceutical company.

episodes.name: The Dentist of Detroit
episodes.overview: Peter and Neal help Mozzie rework a scam to prevent a mob war.

episodes.name: Veiled Threat
episodes.overview: Peter and Neal pose as wealthy bachelors to catch a black widow.

episodes.name: Scott Free
episodes.overview: A teenage con man goes on a New York crime spree.

episodes.name: Taking Account
episodes.overview: When an expert hacker drains a prominent New York bank, Neal assumes the criminal's identity in order to spend the pilfered fortune and draw him out of hiding.

episodes.name: As You Were
episodes.overview: When an old Naval Academy buddy of Agent Jones goes missing, Peter and Neal delve into the dangerous world of international private security to find him.

episodes.name: On the Fence
episodes.overview: Neal goes undercover in an attempt to capture a wanted fugitive; Keller confesses his motive for returning to New York.

episodes.name: Countdown
episodes.overview: Neal and Mozzie must stay ahead of the FBI when one of the treasure's paintings is flagged.

episodes.name: Checkmate
episodes.overview: Elizabeth's kidnapping forces Neal to come clean to Peter about his betrayal.

episodes.name: Upper West Side Story
episodes.overview: Neal poses as a substitute teacher to investigate missing scholarship funds.

episodes.name: Neighborhood Watch
episodes.overview: When Elizabeth overhears one of her neighbors in a suspicious conversation, her curiosity leads Peter and Neal to uncover a robbery plot against a posh Manhattan Hotel.

episodes.name: Pulling Strings
episodes.overview: Sparks fly when Neal teams up with his ex Sara to track down a missing Stradivarius. The mission offers Neal a glimpse into a different kind of life for himself.

episodes.name: Stealing Home
episodes.overview: Neal joins the crew of a wealthy Yankees fan, tasked with stealing memorabilia from Yankee Stadium.

episodes.name: Judgment Day
episodes.overview: Agent Kramer wants to derail Neal's commutation; Neal tries to right a wrong from his past; Peter is forced to choose sides.

3.name: Season 3
3.overview: Suave con man turned FBI consultant Neal Caffrey is racing to stay one step ahead of the feds even as he helps his partner, Agent Peter Burke, bring down some of the world's most clever criminals. The stakes are at an all-time high as Neal struggles to come to terms with his own checkered past, but will his greatest con cost him everything?

episodes.name: Wanted
episodes.overview: Peter tries to find Neal on a remote island before a bounty hunter locates him first.

episodes.name: Most Wanted
episodes.overview: Peter comes up with a strategy to return Neal to the U.S. before Collins catches him.

episodes.name: Diminishing Returns
episodes.overview: The guys track a brilliant thief who's eluded the FBI for years.

episodes.name: Parting Shots
episodes.overview: The team investigates a widow on the verge of an inheritance.

episodes.name: Honor Among Thieves
episodes.overview: A female art thief makes Neal an offer in exchange for important information.

episodes.name: Identity Crisis
episodes.overview: Mozzie, Neal and Peter follow clues left in a storage unit.

episodes.name: Compromising Positions
episodes.overview: A criminal with a vendetta against Peter hires a political fixer to sabotage the trial.

episodes.name: Ancient History
episodes.overview: The team investigates a series of museum heists that target rare artifacts.

episodes.name: Gloves Off
episodes.overview: Neal goes under cover as a stock trader on Wall Street.

episodes.name: Vested Interest
episodes.overview: Peter and Neal pursue one of the paintings on the treasure manifest.

episodes.name: Family Business
episodes.overview: Peter and Neal attempt to find the truth behind Neal's father's crime. In doing so, Neal must go undercover into the world of counterfeit whiskey to take down a high-level member of the Irish Mob.

episodes.name: Brass Tacks
episodes.overview: Peter and Neal look into Senator Pratt's ties to corrupt cops who framed Neal's father and tore his family apart. Their investigation leads them to a real-estate developer running a kickback scheme.

episodes.name: Empire City
episodes.overview: Peter and Neal work a forgery and money laundering case that leads them into two of the most iconic New York institutions, taxi cabs and jazz.

episodes.name: Shoot the Moon
episodes.overview: Peter and Neal work from different angles as they attempt to stop a thieving duo bent on going out in a hail of bullets rather than watch their whirlwind relationship fade away behind bars.

episodes.name: The Original
episodes.overview: Peter and Neal get closer to finding out the mystery behind Ellen's evidence box while simultaneously chiseling their way through the world of sculpture forgery.

episodes.name: In the Wind
episodes.overview: Peter and Neal are one heist away from retrieving the evidence box hidden inside the Empire State Building. Meanwhile, Senator Pratt has enlisted a small army of FBI agents to find the box before Neal.

4.name: Season 4
4.overview: Facing the uncertain future of his partnership with FBI Agent Peter Burke, Neal sheds his tracking anklet and disappears into thin air. But the Feds aren't done with him and Neal is hardly ready for retirement. Back in action, Neal ponders the future as Season Four delves deeper into the stunning secrets of his mysterious past.

episodes.name: At What Price
episodes.overview: With Peter in prison facing murder charges and every shred of evidence pointing to him for Senator Pratt's untimely death, Neal must strike a deal with the devil to help try and clear Peter's name.

episodes.name: Out of the Frying Pan
episodes.overview: Peter assigns Neal a new handler to investigate an online black market, but Neal’s loyalties will be tested when he discovers the trail might lead to Mozzie.

episodes.name: One Last Stakeout
episodes.overview: As Peter settles into a promoted position at the FBI, Neal has to pull off a brazen museum heist right underneath the FBI’s nose.

episodes.name: Controlling Interest
episodes.overview: Peter sends Neal undercover with a psychiatrist who may be manipulating her patients into committing robberies.

episodes.name: Master Plan
episodes.overview: Neal must go undercover as a butler to expose an imposter who aims to inherit a Manhattan family's fortune.

episodes.name: Ice Breaker
episodes.overview: Peter and Neal must go undercover as ice skating pros to expose a counterfeit passport ring in Little Odessa.

episodes.name: Quantico Closure
episodes.overview: While Neal delves further into the mystery of the Codex, Peter takes on a classified espionage case with a fellow FBI agent: his ex-girlfriend.

episodes.name: Digging Deeper
episodes.overview: Neal and Peter take on an unprecedented asset recovery case for the Museum of Natural History: a stolen Tyrannosaurus Rex skeleton and its egg.

episodes.name: No Good Deed
episodes.overview: Peter’s thrown back into an unsolved larceny case that has Neal worried – because Neal’s the one who committed the crime.

episodes.name: Live Feed
episodes.overview: A life hangs in the balance after Hagen tasks Neal with his final assignment.

episodes.name: Shot Through the Heart
episodes.overview: When Neal and Peter go after an assassin, the stakes are raised even higher when they realize this may be the same person who has been pulling Neal’s strings.

episodes.name: Taking Stock
episodes.overview: When a corporate espionage case has personal ties to Neal, Peter recruits Diana from maternity leave for an undercover sting on a rogue stock trader.

episodes.name: Diamond Exchange
episodes.overview: Neal and Peter race against a criminal mastermind to unearth an invaluable treasure hidden in New York.

5.name: Season 5
5.overview: $1.8 million in gold coins is missing, an elusive precious diamond is about to be found, and Neal Caffrey has a new handler – and a new love interest. But all is fair in love and crime, and the closer Neal gets to the mysterious Rebecca Lowe, the greater the danger for everyone in his life.

episodes.name: Borrowed Time
episodes.overview: Peter brings in Rebecca to help locate Neal who's been held captive, by someone she used to work with.

episodes.name: Return to Sender
episodes.overview: Neal must work with an enemy from his past to be able to help the Pink Panther.

episodes.name: Uncontrolled Variables
episodes.overview: Neal is conflicted over scamming an innocent mark. Peter is working with an Interpol agent who could ruin their operation.

episodes.name: All's Fair
episodes.overview: Peter and Neal focus on a case dealing with someone from Mozzie's past.

episodes.name: Whack a Mole
episodes.overview: Neal must orchestrate a treacherous operation for the Pink Panthers on short notice.

episodes.name: Au Revoir
episodes.overview: In order to help Neal carry out a risky heist, Peter must involve himself in a dangerous con.

6.name: Season 6
6.overview: The tension has never been greater as Neal Caffrey re-teams with FBI agent Peter Burke in their most ambitious sting operation yet — infiltrating a sophisticated gang of deadly thieves. With Elizabeth Burke pregnant, Neal desperate for his freedom, and amidst pressure from Mozzie for Neal to cut ties with the FBI, the scheme unfolds, culminating in the series’ most shocking plot twist of all.
